        <h1>UGALI & FISH STEW</h1>

        <div class="recipe-meta">
          <span>‚è± 50 mins</span>
          <span>üçΩ Serves 2</span>
          <span>üí∞ Ksh 250 - 500 Medium Budget</span>
       </div>

        <img src="Images/Ugali and Fish Stew.jpg" alt="Kenyan Fish Stew" loading="lazy">

        <div class="recipe-actions">
            <button onclick="window.print()">üñ® Print Recipe</button>
            <button onclick="shareRecipe()">üîó Share</button>
        </div>

        <p class="category">Category: RECIPE_CATEGORY</p>

        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Tilapia fish, cut into steaks and cleaned</li>
            <li>Onions 2 medium, grated or finely chopped</li>
            <li>Garlic 2 cloves, grated or minced</li>
            <li>Ginger 1 tsp, grated</li>
            <li>Tomatoes 2 large, blended or finely chopped</li>
            <li>Vegetable oil 50 ml (3.4 tbsp)</li>
            <li>Tomato paste 1 tsp</li>
            <li>Curry powder 1.5 tsp</li>
            <li>Coconut cream 15 ml (1 tbsp, optional)</li>
            <li>Fresh coriander chopped for garnish</li>
            <li>Bell peppers 1 mixed (yellow, red, or green), sliced</li>
            <li>Salt To taste</li>
            <li>Maize flour (cornmeal) 4 cups (480 g)</li>
            <li>Water 8 cups (1.9 L) for ugali</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Start by preparing the ugali. In a large pot, bring 8 cups of water to a boil.</li>
            <li>Gradually add the maize flour to the boiling water, stirring continuously to avoid lumps.</li>
            <li>Reduce the heat to low and continue stirring until the mixture thickens and pulls   away from the sides of the pot. This should take about 10-15 minutes. Once done, remove from heat and set aside, keeping it warm.</li>
            <li>Next, prepare the fish stew. Heat the vegetable oil in a large pan  over medium heat.</li>
            <li>Add the grated onions, garlic, and ginger to the pan. Saut√© until the onions are translucent and fragrant, about 5 minutes.</li>
            <li>Add the blended or chopped tomatoes to the pan. Cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the tomatoes break down and form a thick sauce.</li>
            <li>Stir in the tomato paste and curry powder, cooking for another 2    -3 minutes to allow the spices to release their flavors.</li>
            <li>Add the fish steaks to the pan, ensuring they are coated with the sauce.</li>
            <li>If using, pour in the coconut cream to add richness to the stew. Add salt to taste.</li>
            <li>Cover the pan and let the fish simmer in the sauce for about 15-20 minutes, or until the fish is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.</li>
            <li>In the last 5 minutes of cooking, add the sliced bell peppers to the stew for added color and crunch.</li>
            <li>Once the fish is cooked, garnish the stew with freshly chopped coriander.</li>
            <li>To serve, scoop portions of the ugali onto plates and ladle the fish stew over it. Enjoy your Ugali and Fish Stew!</li> 
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>

